{"lemma":"تَعَرُّفاتٌ","slug":"تَعَرُّفاتٌ","root":"ع.ر.ف","root_slug":"ع-ر-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ر-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28728"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8F%D9%91%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become acquainted, with, to meet","examples":[{"text":"تَعَرَّفْنَا فِي الْجَامِعَة.","english":"We got to know each other in college."},{"text":"عِنْدَمَا الْتَقَيْتُ بِهِ لِأَوَّلِ مَرَّةٍ، بَدَأْنَا نَتَعَرَّفُ عَلَى بَعْضِنَا الْبَعْضِ.","english":"When I met him for the first time, we started to get to know each other."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to recognize"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to trace, to discover","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"(for a noun) to be or to become definite"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَعَرَّفَ (taʕarrafa) (form V)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare عَرَفَ (ʕarafa, “to know”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28728","headword_ar":"تعرّف","root":"Erf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, known."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 6.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEr~f A_ilayohi","text_ar":"تعرّف اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made himself known to him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) [and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstErf","text_ar":"استعرف","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotu mutanak~irFA vum~a A@sotaEorafotu","text_ar":"اَتَيْتُ مُتَنَكِّرًا ثُمَّ ا@سْتَعْرَفْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came disguising myself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assuming an unknown appearance, then"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made known who I was:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aiy^oti fulaAnFA","text_ar":"اِيْتِ فُلَانًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA@sotaEorifo A_ilayohi Hat~aY yaEorifaka","text_ar":"فَا@سْتَعْرِفْ اـِلَيْهِ حَتَّى يَعْرِفَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come thou to such a one and make thyself known to him, that he may know thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, K. *) [See also 8.] ―         -b3-  [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEr~f A_ilaY A@ll~`hi biAlEibaAdaAti waAlA^adoEiyapi","text_ar":"تعرّف اـِلَى ا@للّٰهِ بِالعِبَادَاتِ وَالاَدْعِيَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made himself known to God by religious services and prayers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Er-Rághib, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEar~afo A_ilaY","text_ar":"تَعَرَّفْ اـِلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hi fiY Alr~axaA='i yaEorifoka fiY Al$~id~apa","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهِ فِى الرَّخَا=ءِ يَعْرِفْكَ فِى الشِّدَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a saying of the Prophet to Ibn-'Abbás, [may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Make thyself known to God"},{"kind":"text","text":"by obedience"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in ampleness of circumstances,"},{"kind":"text","text":"then"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He will acknowledge thee in straitness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"render thou obedience to God"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c., then]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He will requite thee"},{"kind":"text","text":"[&c.]. (O.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEr~fhu","text_ar":"تعرّفهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He acquainted himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made himself acquainted, with it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him; informed himself of it; learned it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discovered it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"often used in these senses: for an instance of the last, see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tafar~asa","text_ar":"تَفَرَّسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": it is similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEal~amahu","text_ar":"تَعَلَّمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but more restricted in meaning. ―         -b2-  And]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sought the knowledge of it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 6:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did so leisurely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repeatedly, and effectually:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEar~afotu maA Einoda fulaAnK","text_ar":"تَعَرَّفْتُ مَا عِنْدَ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I sought leisurely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repeatedly, after the knowledge of what such a one possessed until I knew it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K. *) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEr~fhu AlmakaAna","text_ar":"تعرّفهُ المَكَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlmakaAni","text_ar":"فِى المَكَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He looked at it, endeavouring to obtain a clear knowledge thereof, in the place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^am~alahu bihi","text_ar":"تَاَمَّلَهُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A3-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEar~ufN","text_ar":"تَعَرُّفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also expl. in the KL by the Pers. words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bErf kArY krdn","text_ar":"بعرف كارى كردن"},{"kind":"text","text":", app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The acting with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eurof","text_ar":"عُرْف"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: but Golius has hence rendered the verb “ convenienter opus fecit. ”]"}],"source_refs":["L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}